column1: #Text=Polycrystalline samples of a series of lanthanide cobalt\riridium oxides Eu2CoIrO6, Tb2CoIrO6 and Ho2CoIrO6\rwere synthesized using the conventional solid-state-\rreaction method.

#Text=Stoichiometric Eu2O3 (99.9 %), Tb4O7\r(99.9 %), Ho2O3 (99.9 %), CoO (99.9 %) and Ir (99.9 %)\rpowders were mixed, ground, pelleted and sintered at\r1100 \C, 1200 \C and 1270 \C for the \frst, second and\rthird sintering, respectively.
#Text=Powder X-ray diraction\r(XRD) measurements were collected on a Rikagu X-ray\rdiraction instrument.
#Text=The XRD data were analyzed by\rRietveld re\fnement using the software MAUD [13].

#Text=Mag-\rnetization was carried out between 2 and 300 K using a\r14 T Quantum Design Physical Property Measurement\rSystem (PPMS) with a vibrating sample magnetometry\r(VSM) option in applied DC magnetic \felds and in a 7\rT Magnetic Property Measurement System (MPMS) Su-\rperconducting Quantum Interference Device (SQUID).
#Text=The pulsed \feld magnetization measurements up to 60\rT were performed at NHMFL in Los Alamos, in which\rthe temperature down to 1.36 K was controlled with a\r4He system.
#Text=The pulsed \feld magnetization data were\rcalibrated against DC measurements.
